    • onSaveClick

      public void onSaveClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      RUNTIME ERROR. Two runtime errors occurred on this method. One was a thrown number format exception. To correct this, I added try and catch clauses where the catch statement displays a general message if the user put text in the incorrect format. The second runtime error was a concurrent modification exception being thrown. The error was caused by the use of an enhanced for loop accessing and modifying items through an observable list. To correct this, I changed the loop to a standard for loop.
      Throws:
      IOException
